class Solution {
    public int[] memLeak(int memory1, int memory2) {
        int crashTime = 0;
        while (memory1 >= crashTime && memory2 >= crashTime) {
            if (memory1 >= memory2) {
                memory1 -= crashTime + 1;
            } else {
                memory2 -= crashTime + 1;
            }
            crashTime++;
        }
        return new int[]{crashTime, memory1, memory2};
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(min(memory1, memory2))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iteratively simulates memory allocation until a crash occurs. It prioritizes allocating memory to the stick with more available memory. The loop terminates when either stick runs out of memory, determining the crash time.

